Subject: Re: [T2] loss of power and really bad sound

On Wed, Sep 24, 2003 at 07:08:05PM -0600, Steve Laughlin wrote:
> On the way home from work my 71 westy had an event which occurred very
> rapidly.  Sudden loss of power but the engine still ran and the ride got real
> rough and noisy.  No engine lights came on but the engine is really running
> rough and power is down considerable, Checking the engine no overt oil leaks
> or anything looking peculiar noted.  Any suggestions on where to start, valve

I would start by verifying that the points didn't close or anything
like that. so, check timing and dwell.

if that is still fine, move to an engine diagnostic. pull the plugs
and do a compression test. that might indicate some engine problems.



